PBG SA (PBG) , Polandâ€™s third-largest
construction company, tumbled to a three-week low after posting
a net loss in the first quarter.  The shares declined as much as 6.7 percent to 21.51 zloty,
the weakest level since April 24, and traded 5 percent lower at
21.9 zloty, at 9:01 in Warsaw. The stock has slumped 69 percent
 this year , underperforming the  WIG20 Index (WIG20) , which slid 2.6
percent.  The builder had a net loss of 60.5 million zloty ($17.5
million) in the first quarter, compared with a 24.1 million-
